                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2122a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-24T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 24, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>297. For the Ambassador and Counselor only. Reference a strictly confidential
                    letter of May 2 from an officer of the Department with five enclosures.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>On an assumption that it should develop that a satisfactory formula
                        containing mutually acceptable pledges and assurances can be worked out,
                        what is your judgment, given the present situation in Japan and in the
                        world, as to (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) the likelihood that any government
                        in Japan could carry out commitments of the character under reference and
                            (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) the likelihood that the Japanese Government
                        would in good faith do so? Also, your opinion as to advisability of this
                        Government making such commitment?</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Your reply should be as “blind” as may be practicable without risk of
                        misunderstanding.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
